---
title: Scenario 7 — Item Re-Enters While Mid-Exit (Re-Entry Race Guard)
---
sequenceDiagram
    participant Service as Backend Service
    participant Cache as SourceCache
    participant Box as AnimatedListBox
    participant Pipeline as Pipeline
    participant ExitAnim as Exit Animation (ghost)
    participant Containers as Container Pool

    Note over Box: Item A is visible at index 1

    Service->>Cache: Remove item A
    Cache-->>Box: CollectionChanged (Remove)
    Box->>Pipeline: Enqueue AddRemove
    Pipeline->>Box: ProcessSnapshot
    Box->>Box: DiffVisible → BeginExit(A)
    Note over ExitAnim: _activeExits[A.id] = handle\nA stays in VisibleItems as ghost\nRunFade(1→0) starts\n_inflightCount = 1

    Note over ExitAnim: ~80ms into 200ms fade

    Service->>Cache: AddOrUpdate item A (re-added)
    Cache-->>Box: CollectionChanged (Add) after 150ms throttle

    Box->>Box: ClassifyChange → AddRemove
    Box->>Pipeline: Enqueue AddRemove

    Note over Pipeline: Pipeline is busy (exit animating)\nEnqueue and wait

    ExitAnim->>ExitAnim: Animation completes\n_inflightCount--

    Box->>Box: onComplete callback fires\nCheck: _activeExits.ContainsKey(A.id)?
    Note over Box: YES — still registered\n_activeExits.Remove(A.id)\nVisibleItems.RemoveAt(IndexOfById(A.id))\nA fully gone from VisibleItems

    Box->>Pipeline: OnAllAnimationsComplete\n_pipelineBusy = false
    Pipeline->>Pipeline: TryProcessNext\nDequeue AddRemove (re-add A)

    Pipeline->>Box: ProcessSnapshot
    Box->>Box: DiffVisible\nA not in VisibleItems → insert
    Box->>Containers: PrepareContainerForItemOverride

    Note over Containers: No active exit for A\n(it was cleaned up above)\nResetVisuals() — clean state
    Containers->>Containers: ConsumeEntryReason(A.id)\n→ Default (no stamp)\nRunFade(0→1)

    Note over Box: A fades back in cleanly

    Note over Box: --- DANGEROUS VARIANT ---
    Note over Box: What if re-add arrives BEFORE exit completes?

    Note over ExitAnim: Exit still running at t=80ms

    Pipeline->>Pipeline: _pipelineBusy = true (exit running)\nAddRemove waits in queue

    ExitAnim->>ExitAnim: Exit completes at t=200ms
    Box->>Box: onComplete: _activeExits.ContainsKey(A.id) = true\nRemove ghost → clean
    Box->>Pipeline: Gate releases

    Pipeline->>Box: Process re-add → PrepareContainer
    Containers->>Containers: _activeExits.TryGetValue(A.id) = false\n(already cleaned)\nSafe to animate entry

    Note over Box: No race — exit always completes\nbefore re-add processes\nbecause pipeline is gated
